Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations:

Overview Notes: Diet, exercise, non smoker. Moderate alcohol intake. Loves job. Good life balance.

Overview Notes: Supplement with methylated B vitamins : Phytomulti and Omega 3's - Metagenics.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Repeat homocysteine, ALT, Lipogram in 3 months.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment

Special Investigation Notes: Recent testicular trauma, now dysuria++. urine sent for mc+s

Women's Health Recommendations:

Overview Notes: Supplement with methylated B vitamins : Phytomulti and Omega 3's - Metagenics.
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: We will do your cholesterol when we repeat other abnormal parameters in 3 months. For now start Omega and Phytomulti, increase greens and resistance training.
Special Investigation Notes: Recent testicular trauma, now dysuria++. urine sent for mc+s

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Strong family history of heart disease on your Dad's side with young heart attacks and high cholesterol. Your diet is high in natural fats so not an issue. please try to source pasture fed organic meat and eat more greens and veggies. Also discussed adding more resistance training for bone vitality and strength.
Comment Key: MentalHealthNote
Comment Value: None

Overview Notes: Supplement with methylated B vitamins : Phytomulti and Omega 3's - Metagenics.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations:
